caption: Great atmosphere and German fusion.

Funkenhausen came recommended by a friend and it did not disappoint. The menu is rather abbreviated but the selections do not disappoint. I like that it’s not overflowing with choice. The food was absolutely delicious. We tried the pretzel, brat, and spätzle for appetizers and then I had the chicken schnitzel as an entree. Dinner portions were definitely adequate. The atmosphere is really chique with some German props in good taste placed through the restaurant. Five stars in my book!
I got the piggy plate but I will get the pork chop next time.
Food was really tasty and the service was excellent
Great food and cocktails. Even better service!
The food is great and the delicious beer flows freely. Next time we've got to get Das Boot!
Good food, good vibes, great service. Very friendly and attentive. 10/10 would recommend.

Nice small area, I love the outdoor seating. Service was great. I ordered the short rib. It was really rich and delicious, but hard to finish without some sort of starch. Had to knock one star off for that. Otherwise, great ambiance for a date or catching up with friends.

This place is so amazing. Great customer service and yummy food! We ordered the steak with crab as well as the seafood paella. The price was reasonable and the view was impeccable. Would definitely come back again and enjoy their other items.

Chocolate cake and apple cobbler were nice as was the pretzel. The happy hour offerings were good value for money. The piggy platter felt like a let down in comparison to the happy hour offerings/ other starters in general.
Great food and service! Possibly the best potato side I've ever had. Desserts extra solid as well.

I think as a European maybe things didn’t appeal quite as much to me as I’ve had access to German food my whole life. The ribs are REALLY good and everyone who goes there should try them! I wasn’t blown away by the chicken sandwich and the beer was a bit pricey but the general atmosphere and service was good. As a Brit I wouldn’t rush back here but I can see it’s appeal.

Enjoyed their brunch a lot, their French toast and spatzel dishes are great! The food is always really good, and the quality is amazing. It is a bit pricey for the amount that you get, but again, the quality is great! I have never had anything I didn't like. Definitely a nice date spot or "treat yourself" occassion, but not an everyday restaurant for me (but I think that's what they are going for).

The ambience was really nice and intimate. Went with a bunch of my girlfriends. They had a great wine selection and it is tapas style of food. We ordered a bunch of dishes that we all shared. The portion size was enough and flavor was perfect. Out of all the dishes, I really enjoyed the Vegan Carrot Taquitos and the Baked Brie!

Ordered the spaetzle bolognese and they used dried, packaged spaetzle. The photo of the meal shows homemade spaetzle. The flavors were really good, but the texture was bad. Packaged spaetzle soaks up more moisture so it was mushy when it arrived. That's just not cool. Give this place a chance, but order something else.
Food was delicious. Service never overbearing. Definitely will be back!!!
Excellent food. Friendly service.
Delicious food, fabulous service and socially distanced.
Great service,circuses and great recipes. Very enjoyable

We love Funkenhausen! Ordered the Prix Fixe last night (Sweet Corn, Smoked Chicken, and Cobbler) and a side of ribs. I walked over with my son, and forgot my mask, but they were so accommodating. We did contactless pickup and they hung a mask for my way back on the bag. The sweet corn is a creamed corn that is delish! We always love the ribs, and the panzanella that comes with the chicken is great as well. In the winter they have a chicken and dumplings that I can't wait to get again. And their hot boozy cider :)

At the moment  you arrive in this place  they give you an agreeable feeling. Very warm hosts, it is a happy restaurant to  pass time with friends and colleagues or with your date. tasty  cooking, talented  chef de cuisine, decent  cost and excellent  service. Warmly recommended.
Food isn’t very good
Never a bad meal, wine list is tops, and das boot...you gotta get it!
Always quality, but poor service
Great drink choices and upbeat atmosphere! Phenomenally kind/cool staff!!
All fantastic - great food, great drinks and great service!
Great value and quality, staff and atmosphere are fun upbeat
The food and service were both on point
First time, really liked the food. Can't wait to go back. Pretzels were fantastic.

We went there ,When we were in Chicago for brunch during restaurant week. Bright atmosphere. Amazing new style German food with excellent service. Great & Inventive cocktails plus point .Highly recommend !
Very neat and welcoming place. They provide big portions and for reasonable rates. I liked the food very much and the staff were very affable and informative. Will definitely recommend this spot.
Love everything about this place! Amazing food, service and atmosphere!
Food and service was amazing
German inspired food. Perfect base for a day of drinking.
Great food! Also loved the free round of mimosas :)
This place obviously knows how to take care of their clients. Always with a helpful demeanor. The food is reasonably priced, constantly flavorful and neat.
2nd time weve been here for brunch. Good drinks and modern german fair. Biscuits were tender and buttery. Spaetzle was great too. Good bloody Mary and breakfast cocktails. Nom

Don't be afraid of the idea of traditional German food by way of Nashville - it works. Despite living only a block away, it took us over a year to try out this decided different offering on Chicago Avenue. Five of us went for Sunday. Every dish represented a Southern take on a decidedly German dish. We are a "can I have a bite of yours" family, and everyone was impressed with each dish ordered.
Amazing new style German food with excellent service. Gone twice in the past couple months and both times were exceptional. Cool and trendy interior. Highly recommend.

Read the menu first! This place isn't for everyone as the cuisine is on the adventurous side. After being here a few times, I would recommend the HAUS SALAD with the DRY AGED SLAGEL PORK CHOP. Went with 4/5 stars because the drink prices are outrageous.

Went for brunch during restaurant week. Bright atmosphere. Seating is a bit close together so be prepared to share your conversation with your neighbors. The fare was exactly what I would expect of a german spot. Good comfort food. Only complaint is the price of beverages.

Very noisy on a Sunday brunchtime. Servers were pleasant, efficient, and the food came fast! Everyone in my party of five but me was happy with their food. I ordered a biscuit and some grits (trying to relive my misspent youth in Georgia). The biscuit was huge and it was okay, nothing out of the ordinary. The grits were...strange. Tasted a bit like there was a dairy product in there that had gone off. The seltzer I ordered did not come with free refills, so it was $6 for two seltzers. Not saying I wouldn't give it a second chance since everyone else was happy, but I'd definitely come when it was quieter.
Contemporary German food. It's a nice place for all occasions.
Very clean and friendly staff. Food was designed differently than how I read the menu, delightful!
Great food, fast service and really nice atmosphere.
Amazing service and incredible food
The Fried Giardiniera might be one of the best appetizers I've ever had
Very trendy
Spaetzle carbonara was amazing.
Tasty and fun

You can’t miss at Funkenhausen, excellent beers and modern southern fusion German food. Do yourself a favor and get some pretzels and charcuterie. This is a place that’s equally fun at the bar and at a table
Wow this place is so great. The space, the food, the pace. Will be thinking about that chicken for a while...
We had a combination of dishes and most were just ok with one being good and one being bad.
Best German bar around
Meh, overpriced, small servings, indifferent service.  Place where people are more interested in taking pix of the food than eating it.
Cool bar with excellent bartenders! Interesting cocktails and neat looking space.

I like to go with friends to this place with my highest recommendations. I go their often. I get very good feedback from my friends. The meals are appetizing and the stuff is efficient and cooperative. Whenever we visit this place we enjoy a pleasant evening.  I warmly recommend this restaurant.
Great staff, prompt service. Clean and cute place. Good food.
A fun take on German dishes, this West Town spot is great for date night. Loved their charcuterie!
Excellent food and one of the servers in the game John Casto...what more do you need for a good night out?
Service at the bar was efficient, but not very warm. The atmosphere was my favorite part - funky and sleek. Happy hour deals weren't phenomenal.
Fun place with great food. A delicious modern take on traditional German fare!
This restaurant has amazing service and delightful food. My favourite spot around town. The drinks and food served rapidly and the rates are affordable. Highly recommended.
Everything was great.  Service, food, ambiance, house cocktails.  This was my 2nd time and I will gladly go back.
I just enjoy their dishes. I always get great service there. The place is always clean and the workers are always friendly. Will come back again.
Delectable saucy smoky salty

Wow. Freaking fantastic! I had high expectations and they were exceeded. The Sunday Schnitzel was incredible. The sweat breads and giant pasta pillow and pig plate we're also huge hits. The beer was good and the boot shots were campy and fun but good. The management and team were all super personable and friendly. I took my mom here to cheer her up and they went above and beyond anything I could hope for. I can't recommend this place enough and will be coming here regularly more. A+ 5 stars 10/10.
Very well kept and welcoming restaurant. They serve big meals and for fair rates. I liked the menu a lot and the staff members were very attentive and informative. I recommend this place.

Wow. A completely different take on German classics, thanks to the southeastern US/BBQ components fused. The balance between crunchy and soft, spicy/salty and sweet is expertly done in a way not typically found in either root cuisine. It is uncommon to find well-done Carolina/Tennessee/Alabama-style food in these parts and not THAT common to find great German food EITHER (forget Hofbrau or Berghof), and this is greater than the sum of its parts.  My only quibble is that the menu could be bigger, or more configurable, including portion sizes. For instance, I had a pretzel with pimento cheese and white BBQ (sweet mustard - based) for dipping... Both were fantastic, but neither was present in many other entrees. The Nashville hot schnitzel special (Sunday only) comes a la carte with 2 GIANT tenderloins, way too much for almost any person, and no sides. I bought a $10 side of too-much Käsespätzle... If I could have purchased a meal with 1 tenderloin and a 1/2 portion of Käsespätzle, that would have been perfect, and still extremely generous. Beer and wine selections are great too.  I will definitely be back when I am in the Ukrainian Village area, and suggest you do the same.
Love this place. Two of my favorite cuisines (German and US Southern) fused together. Frequent menu updates, great drink and wine choices, and amazing atmosphere.  No complaints.
Absolutely a place worth stopping by, the food is awesome and fresh, the cost is reasonable and it is constantly clean there. Keep up the good work.

Came in on a Tuesday for happy hour and I am so happy and satisfied. Tuesday is also their burger special and it's seriously one of the best burgers in Chicago, and I know that gets thrown around a lot.  The happy hour has lots of delicious small bites and specials on beers, a house cocktail and wine. The bar area is large so it's easy to get a spot. I've had dinner a few times prior and loved the food and service each time. This place is amazing. Best new restaurant as of late.

The space is fun and well decorated! We enjoyed the atmosphere and the help from the staff. The only thing was that the food was disappointing. We went on a Monday night during happy hour and sat at the bar. The garlic pretzel tasted dry and stale like it was at least a day old. The beef tips were so dry it was like sucking water out from a rock. The catfish was tasty as were the scallops. The schnitzel hot chicken sandwich was easily the best thing. All in all we left a little underwhelmed. I was looking forward to this meal as it was listed as a 2020 bib gourmand.
Love the food, and service was top notch! Will definitely come again.
The Sunday Nashville Hot Chicken Schnitzel was the highlight! Good German beer selection. Everything I ate there was wonderful!

We came here for brunch and I am so glad we did! We sat at the bar and service was fast and wonderful. The bloody marys are delicious and so is the food! You must try the Carbonara - it is amazing! Will definitely be coming back here and would love to try their dinner menu.
Service Great .. PBJ donut needs pb on side for those of us who can eat nuts. Maple Surup Real .. Nice touch. cool place eclectic menu.
great service, food and beer selection had something for everyone, easy to get to location.  Must have the broccolini
Food was really, really good, and the service was just great. And on top of that, I thought the price was just right. Can't wait to go back!
I actually love their food and service, great area very close to my apartment. The cashiers are always very welcoming. Highly recommended.

Our server was top shelf. Not pushy but exceptionally knowledgeable. The food was out of this world. German food is not known for taking you to Flavortown. But this did. Smoky broccolini? Check. Perfect ribs with a bechemel sauce? Check. This is a must visit.
One of the best in Chicago. Food is always good. Javier is the best bartender in the city.

Food is outstanding!  Hostess is a bit stand offish even if you have reservations and there are tables open, so we chose to sit at the bar and loved it!  Too many dishes for us to get through, so we'll be back!
Cute restaurant. Good food.
Always a go to when I'm in Chicago. The food and service are great and it's such a great atmosphere!
The place offers an awesome range of delicious food. I enjoyed eating here. Staff members are always super friendly, prices are affordable and the spot is always neat.
Went in to sample the happy hour, enjoyed it so much we got some items off of the main menu and called it dinner. Awesome food, drinks and service at exceptional values. Highly recommended!!!
This place sure knows how to treat their clients. Constantly with a very friendly approach. The food is fairly priced, always delicious and neat.
Fantastic and yummy food, I love the mood this spot has, and the cashiers were kind. Will surely come back again.
great brunch spot,  reasonable prices.  great atmosphere
Love the decor, beer selection, and food. Staff is accommodating and super friendly. Try a German beer!

Unique blend of South Carolina and German cuisine, prepared flawlessly in a casual setting. The funkenbrunchen has great brunch options, with an eye towards unique flavors. This Palmetto State resident with German ties approved.
The restaurant is excellent and roomy, the meals was enchanting and the rates were very affordable. quickly, effective service and very affable staff members. Highly recommended.
Ate some lunch at the bar. Enjoyed the food, drinks and atmosphere. You have to know when to twist the boot. (movie reference)
Good food and atmosphere. Das boot das good.
Most Excellent Food! Highly Recommend The Pork Chop!
Marvelous place, casual friendly servers, delicious food.

When I think of food Southern cuisine gets a 2 thumbs up and German...well, meh. But this place gave me all the feels. Service was excellent!!!!! The oysters were delicate and fried-say what?!?! The chicken was one of the tastier dishes which says a lot because other than the Publican chicken and Thomas Keller’s, chicken can be a boring dish. The wine list leaned into Austria, different for Chicago in a good way. Honestly, everything was delish- quail, broccolini, etc. The biggest attraction for me was the attention to detail in the veggies. A+ Oh and the dessert was Southern Hummingbird cake riff. Yes please.
Delicious modern take on German food. I loved the surfenturfen and the pork chops but honestly everything we got here was great!

Overall a nice space, but didn't live up to my expectations.  I came with a group of friends on a Monday night. The half off bottle of wine deal was pretty great, but our waiter strangely kept the bottle away from the table so we always had to ask him for a refill.  We ordered two pretzels to share as a group. I really liked the white BBQ sauce, but the pretzel itself was a bit dry.  My friends seemed to like their own dishes, especially the surfenturfen. However, I was less than impressed with my spare ribs. Though they were appropriately tender, the dish lacked any bold or memorable flavors.  I might return but I would definitely order something else if I did.
In general, it lives up to the hype.
Good but not great, better than average
We went on a Tuesday when they have their burger special, was delicious. Amish chicken and broccolini are also amazing and the service was great!
LOVE me some good pretzels. Happy hour is amazing! I work close by and I love visiting after a long day for some delicious happy hour drinks.
One of the best breakfasts I've had.

Absolutely one of the best places to eat in Chi. Unreal. The food is exactly what you need when you want food that represents a place perfectly, but yet has their own flavors. The cologne style beer service is so amazing. Can’t get enough. Go here!
Ribs are bae.

Funkenhausen lives up to its name, it's the best restaurant. My favorite in IL. Had a mix of different plates and wow it was delicious. The spaghetti, tomato and plum salad, and pasta varieties were mouth watering. This is a great place to eat with friends, go on a romantic date, or dine in with your entire family. I'll be back again!!
The food was phenomenal. The service, average.
Solid
These guys are killing it, do yourself a favor and stop there!

German food with southern hospitality. I loved all of the food. The Wunder Under was such a perfectly balanced cocktail I will go back for that alone. The Sunday schnitzel special was awesome, although beware of the strong dill if you're not a fan.

Had the corn and poached peach dessert. Was okay, not memorable. Service was great so that made up for the unimpressive dessert. They have great hours and it's a large space. I will go back for the yummy chicken drumstck dish that I tried at an event.
The food and drink options were excellent!  I highly recommend the ricotta dumplings!
Great service and wonderful food! Prost!

Four of us ate a Funkenhausen for the first time. We ordered a variety of items, mostly small plates but also one large plate. Honestly, the large plate serving size (Scottish Salmon) wasn't much different from the smaller plates. The salmon and the Sturgeon Pastrami were good but not exceptional, but everything else (Haus salad, broccolini, potato salad, pretzel, spare ribs, burratta) was delicious. The service was great and the wine recommendations were spot on. I'd definitely recommend this restaurant.
The food is exceptional. Happy hour is amazing.
Everything we had was great, waiter was phenomenal

The creamed corn is PHENOMENAL! Get it, you won't regret it. I can't stop thinking about how amazing it was! Javier was a great server and the other food and drink was great. But really, it's all about that corn!
Great experience, amazing food, cold beer!!!

Updated review: great new happy hour. Excited to try the full menu sometime. Great service as well.  Edit: kinda wish they brought back the garlic pretzel monkey bread or whatever it was. I prefer it over the new pretzel. If that was $5 on the happy hour menu I'd be all over it
Awesome food.  Awesome staff.  Reasonable prices for the quality that you are getting.
Food is amazing. Service and drinks are great. Love the vibe.

Came here at the recommendation of a friend and it did not disappoint. The service was excellent, very friendly and helpful. The food was also delicious. We ordered several  "small" plates - ribs, carrots, spatzle, and a pretzel. The ribs were excellent, would absolutely recommend them. The pretzel was fine (not spectacular). I really enjoyed the spatzle as it was deliciously cheesy and flavorful. My table mates loved the carrots. They have a nice acidity to them. Unique dishes and reasonably priced. Would highly recommend.
Great spot. Good cocktails and food. Being pescatarian is risky going to a German place but they hit the nail on the head!
Awesome small plates, cool vibes. Highly recommend!

A truly amazing restaurant, with some of the most delicious food and the kindest waitstaff. Our experience was perfect: we ordered many drinks and many dishes, and they were all delightful. Thank you, Funkenhausen, for an enjoyable and a one-of-a-kind dining experience!
The atmosphere and food we had was great. The service top notch.  Very interesting menu we had the pork plate and the white barbecue sauce spare ribs.  They were fall off the bone tender.
The food, the people, and the atmosphere are all wonderful. We go here almost once per week, either to eat or just have drinks. Love it!!
Delicious! I would definitely come back again
super dope, very costly
Food tastes good but was lukewarm.
Been here a couple times the food is nothing special many of the dishes look very blah and boring prepare to leave here hungry and feeling robbed

This place is super interesting! Beautiful place overall, a mix of modern and German antiqueyness. Was here for brunch and it was so comfy you could overstay your welcome . Food was well executed and tasty. Didn't have any drinks but the menu looked great. Service was fantastic and I'll definitely be back.

Great food and beer. The food on the big plates is pricey but can be shared with a couple of people. The food is delicious. We had the borccolini dish and the chicken, both were fantastic. I highly recommend this restaraunt to anyone in the area.
Love the interior. Friendly staff and great food.

I visited here with my partner and another couple on a Sunday evening. We had a wonderfully attentive and knowledgeable server who took great care of us. Between the four of us we ordered about three quarters of the menu. Our whole party enjoyed every aspect of our dining experience, food, drinks and dessert. Looking forward to visiting again!

I thought that they did a fantastic job. The food was good, the presentation was excellent.  We had Jesse as our waiter and his service was attentive and knowledgeable.  We loved him What a great use of the space too.  Not too crowded or noisy.

Thoroughly impressed with this restaurant. All around A+ experience from the very friendly staff, attentive service, and the food was absolutely unique and tasty. One of the best restaurant experiences we have been to while on our extended stay in Chicago. Definitely will be back soon!
Good beer selection. Nice ambiance. Mains were okay but flavors not as developed as the sides.

I loved funkenhausen! We started with the piggy plate- which is a charcuterie board that had all house made meats. Chicken liver mousse, porchetta, bacon, a beef sausage, kielbasa, and apple butter and mustard with a variety of pickles. A chilled asparagus and fennel salad  that was perfectly cooked (asparagus was so tender!) and featured some delicious lumps of crab. We also had the flat bread with ricotta, leeks, and bacon, which was nice (since I was so hungry) but in hindsight I wish we'd ordered something in place of this. After that we had the lamb entree and the ricotta dumplings with it. Both were impeccable dishes. The lamb was especially tender and surprisingly filling! We finished with some raspberry tart crisp dish that was a very pleasant end to a meal we all washed down with different glasses of riesling. The entire experience was made all the more enjoyable by our playful server who made some great recommendations (including helping us not to over order)! I can't wait to come back here!
My boys picked this place for Mother's Day brunch. We each ordered something different. Everything was excellent. Definitely, will be going back.
A truly funky (and amazing) fusion of German and Southern styles. I highly recommend the spare ribs.
Great Service and food!

First time here and I know it will not be the last.  We ordered the charcuterie plate which was delicious.  5 different meats, ham, pickled carrots and zucchini.  It was so great but my favorite was the sausage. Yum!  I then had the whole mess of chicken with oyster mushrooms, my favorite, and wow.  The sauce was perfect and the mushrooms incredible.  Though my friends and I were the only ones at a table, the bar was full.  Happy hour seems to be a hit here.  Their brunch looks awesome so I will come back for that soon!  The waiter was very attentive but not overly so, so that's a huge plus.  Answered all our questions well.  The drinks were perfect.

We went to a close by empty Bohemian restaurant close by with no drink specials and wonky service. We walked into Funkenhausen and it was packed and vibe was already set. Happy Hour  was hopping! Healthy pours of the Rose also helped too! Try the German pizza and I swear you’ll dream about it!
Omg this place was awesome. Great food and great wine!
Hostess was very short and disrespectful over the phone.  Service was excellent  Food was excellent  Would go again
Cool vibes and good food, but prices are a little to high for what you get
The ribs, asparagus and pork shoulder and almond dessert are not to be missed!
Cocktails expertly crafted, if a bit pricey.
Amazing service and phenomenal unique take on traditional German food.
Service was fantastic, drinks were great, and food was even better. Had the shrimp und grits and was very pleased. Will def go back.
(Translated by Google) Schnitzel. Get it.  (Original) Schnitzel. Get it.
Great food, service, atmosphere, and drinks. Get the ribs!
Everything we had was stellar, recommend the Piggy Plate and the Oysters Hockafeller!
The food, service & atmosphere was perfect!

Reserved a table on Open Table on a Saturday morning at 10:30am. I wouldn't be worried about doing a walk in because it's a spacious place so there wouldn't be much of a wait. Interior is beautiful!  Got the Schnitz and Gritz, Dad's Crepes, and Oma's Breakfast. Everything was pretty good. Wouldn't say any of it was amazing, but it did the job in a nice environment.  It's also next door to Beatnik. Fun Fact.  Might come back for dinner because I've heard the Dinner menu is much better than the Brunch one. So fingers crossed
Coolest bartenders in the biz. Shoutout to Ken!

Fun place for German food with a twist. Really enjoyed the sturgeon pastrami & the smelts/asparagus small plate was fantastic. The "tarte flambe" was good, but honestly more of a flat bread than a tarte. Definitely try the smoked spare ribs, those were great.  Great & inventive cocktails, and since they focus on wine to match the region if the food, you will likely find something you've never heard of...give it a try  Seems like a place that will change a few menu items petty frequently, but will keep their core menu the same.  Service was great, thank you for a wonderful experience.
The service was excellent.  The pork shoulder and charcuterie board were really good.  The old fashioned was bad.
Good beer, a little busy and noisy lacking a bit on the atmosphere but we also lined up with a 1 year olds bday party.

My experience with German food has always been on the bland side. That is not the case with Funkenhausen. Every dish was flavorful and delicious! The atmosphere and decor are lovely. Will definitely be back.
Fantastic. Everything was amazing.
Simply amazing food, some of the best brunch I've ever had. Stellar cocktails, too!
Fish schnitzel, who knew?
Great selection and delicious food

Great service and good food! Different, but not enough so that you can’t visit often! I went for brunch this past weekend and the sweet potato/pork belly was amazing! For dinner, my favs are the Oysters, Broccollini, Surfenturfen and the spare ribs. Yummm

Just had an amazing brunch at Funkenhausen yesterday. The food was top notch, we split the carbonara (with egg you break yourself) and croque madam. Both were super indulgent and delicious. Our friends had salads and both loved them too. We'll be back to try dinner next time. The decor was also a treat, bright refreshing interior design.  Brunch was very affordable when split, but I'm seeing how dinner could maybe add up when looking at the menu. We shall see.

I love this place. But now I love it even more since I had brunch y'day. The pig plate for dinner is always our go to. Last time we had the risotto...it was meh. It needed....salt. But I doubt I'll ever go back for dinner (because it's much easier to brunch with my 2 yr old) and the brunch was AMAZING. Swedish pancakes we're a little sweet for my liking but the schnitz and grits and croque madame were the bomb Diddy!!!!  I can't wait to go back and try the smoked trout plate, omas bfast and the spatzele. The crispy potatoes are to die for. I can't wait till 10 am Sunday.
Food is good nothing special.  New style, with bar and restaurant halves.

Had a great experience here for brunch. Service was good, great decor, and good beer selections.  I’d highly recommend the “oma’s breakfast” - it was a great sampler of what they had to offer. 10/10.  The Schnitz and Grits was flavorful and good, but the breading on the meat was soggy, even in areas without the gravy. 6/10.  The donut was great and fit for sharing. The cherries on top added a great touch of tart. 9/10.  I definitely want to come back and try dinner - hopefully the schnitzel I had was just a bad batch.
Delicious and fun!
Fantastic experience!  The pork shoulder and piggy plate were outstanding, but the charred broccoli dish stole the show.
Delicious food! Who knew German and southern comfort food would mesh so we'll together!
A fun place for a small plate dinner. Highly recommend sharing plates. Unique fusion of foods!

Food was amazing!  Chef uses spices in a very creative, refreshing way.  Piggy plate was awesome.  Highly recommend.  Service was s bit slow, but think our waitress had a few too many tables.  Would definitely go again
Great food and great drinks and great service, especially tiger!
Just okay food and just okay service.
Loved it all! The food, atmosphere and drinks.

I had no clue that there's a German themed restaurant in Chicago...I was so surprised! The food was fantastic and the staff was very friendly and patient 😉😅... I will definitely come again!  Greetings from Germany✌️

Came here for brunch with some friends from the neighborhood. I like the open kitchen- the staff was very nice. The food came out quickly and was delicious. I ordered the schnitzel and grits and it was seasoned very well, although the grits were a little cold- I wasn't watching the kitchen- so I don't know if it was waiting or was just plated on a cold plate. My friends both really liked their dishes- one vegetarian broccolini dish and a croque madame.  I wished I'd have ordered the croque madame after seeing it come out & would order that next time instead.
Food was delicious. Portion sizes are decent, but you may want to order an extra app
Wow the food was really well done. Best German food I've had really ever.  Spaetzle, pork, and especially the  chicken were super tasty.
Brunch is very impressive. Everything is tasty!
Lovely mix of German style with southern flare
Great service, friendliest staff!

Really friendly staff, delicious food with a bit of a funky twist — try the sturgeon pastrami! The whole mess of chicken is has a creamy mushroom gravy and perfectly moist smoked chicken—this is what Campbell’s cream of mushroom soup wants to be when it grows up.
Cool atmosphere with great food and great beer.

Next time I'll take photos but I always eat it too fast. Great place to sit at the bar with a small party or by yourself. It's fun to watch the bar tenders make cocktails and they are so friendly! I do recommend going with at least one more person for sharing and increased dishes to taste. It's organized like a Girl and the Goat or Parachute where there are larger plates and smaller plates and you grab a collection and share them, but everything has the german tilt. The spatzel is amazing. Ricotta dumplings are on fire with the pulled pork and bacon pieces. Some of the best scallops I've had out on the surfenturfen, and the pork belly.... showstopper. Great beer list, and coffee and tea for after to help you digest. Don't be proud, take the help. It's a heavy and delicious time :)

My mother was born in Saraland. My father was born in Southern Florida. I came to brunch for my birthday and thoroughly enjoyed it. The schnitz and grits took me all the way back to my roots. I loved the food. The staff and chef were very friendly and efficient. I am definitely coming back again.
Really nice spot. We enjoyed their restaurant week menu. It was a nice kind of busy - the space had a great energy about it.

Simple yet fresh environment, details in the dinning room, bar and bathroom make it pleasing. Javier was my bartender, cool cat. Kept it simple ans fresh. Honestly cant remember what cocktails I consumed, so many yah know? Lol I do remember thinking, "well damn, this is great!" Proceeded to order at will. If I remember correctly, Javier even let me try a "test cocktail", nice special moment! Will be back.
The ambiance was terrific - lovely space. Great beers and cocktails.

Very good. The advantages of Chicago Restaurant Week, when you get to try restaurants more abundantly and relatively less expensive.  The menu is about german food preoared with alittle twist. The pork chacuterie was stupendous. Spaetzle was excellent. Schnitzel was crispy and tender.   Will ve back
Cool spot
Fun, "funky" (yeah) modern Southern/German cuisine. Foodie in a good way, cheerful boisterous vibe. We had very nice service.
Im not a huge brunch person but this place is amazing! Loved their scrambled eggs with cheese and onions (not on menu) and Swedish Pancakes!
Fun menu with great adult beverage choices. Smaller menu that is very well put together and thoughtful, 100% will go again.
Pretty big tasty portions, ok price, European-Cajun mix. Will surely come back!
Fantastic food, great beer but what make the experience even better for me was our knowledgeable, kind and considerate waiter Jesse.
Good food! Service is very casual and the tables are on top of each other
Nice place good service food is tasty
The spare ribs were fantastic, great service overall
Great place. Highly recommend.

Fantastic. I'm not a fan of German cuisine in general so I went in with low expectations that were wildly exceeded. We split the garlic salted pretzel knots, french onion spaetzle and smoked short ribs.  The ribs might be the best I have ever had. The service was good and the kitchen even comped us an extra garlic pretzel knots because we were a group of three. My Pics are half portions because I couldn't wait to eat
Killer pork dishes. Surfenturfen, ribs, and piggy board were especially excellent. Cocktails we're very good as well!
The food and drinks are good but too heavy! I love the donuts and coffee more! After I ate my food I couldn’t finish the whole and I was stuffed! So you can get one for two with appetizers.
Wonderfully delicious German fusion fare
Really good food and interesting cocktails.
Great food exelen service!!!!! Great place🐷🐷😄😄😄

I first heard of Funkenhausen on a food review playing on the payment screen in the back of a cab. I don’t recall the exact dishes they showcased, but the few minutes of footage I saw was enough for me to come in and check it out.  My boyfriend and I came in for a really early dinner (5pm). We thought we’d be the only ones in there, but after 10 minutes of being seated I turned around and the place was packed.  The atmosphere was fun, modern, spacious, not too loud and nicely lit. The food prep station was clean and it was clear that the staff had very good attention to detail when it came to presentation.  The service was great! Our server was awesome and helped a couple of semi-hungry newbies decide what to order based on our liking and appetite. Had the oysters, carpaccio, “the other artichoke” and pretzel. All pretty light and not too heavy. For drinks we ordered an old fashioned and something with tequila in it :) We wanted beers for our second round, but were not familiar with what was on the menu. We gave him an idea of what kind of beer we liked and his suggestions for each of us was right on!  We wanted dessert to-go. The server insisted we experienced the carrot roll plated and take a few bites before he boxed it up so we could appreciate the presentation. Much appreciated!  We will definitely be back. Thank you!

First off, the scallop is remarkable, it was cooked perfect throughout its thickness, it complements the bite-size pork bellys that come with it, and the size is just about right for two people to share. I ordered a cocktail with gin and vermouth (pretty much a negroni) that goes very well with both the scallop-and-pork and the sweet potatoes, our second starter. The drink comes in an etched glass, looks good with the pretty candle on the table and the 20s-style wall lamps that made the ambiance. The server and the hostess were courteous and helpful but not intruding. We had a good time!
Fun place, unique food
Funkenhausen is great. The staff is so kind and accommodating, the food is delicious, and the atmosphere is lovely. We will certainly be back.

First, the place is awesome looking, the beer selection is great and delicious. The menu looks fantastic too and service was A+. However, the entré I ended up ordering (trout) was underwhelming. Flavors of the trout itself were great but the "pretzel" that comes with it was the size of a toddlers fist and had to order more, made me feel like they were being cheap with the portions.  For $14-$15 bucks that plate should be at another level, take Steingold's pretzels as an example or even the Publican.

Food: delicious and creative in flavor, texture and presentation Drink: pretty large offering of beers on tap, cans, bottles, wines - all German brands Service: kind, knowledgeable and humorous. Was accommodating in providing recommendations and coursing out the dishes. Ambiance: hipster swanky (if that’s a thing) and not too loud  I would highly recommend!
Modern take on German cuisine.  Refined and well executed.
Unbelievable dishes. Fantastic flavors. Comfort food elevated ❤️❤️❤️

The food here was delicious and unique. We went early because we had our 1yr old with us. She loved the food as much as we did! I loved the German beer menu. Lots of great options. Our waiter was also a really nice guy who we ended up having a couple longer conversations with. Very sociable and nice guy!
Really good brunch with some original options (try the sweet potato dish).
VERY cool joint! German Vacation in Mexico. Charred broccolini. Chicken. Great service from Daniella!
Had an excellent experience this past Saturday. Food was phenomenal as was the service. Highlights were the Blue Plate Spaetzle, Surfenturfen, and Weiss Wurst. Great for groups. Will be back.
Nice vibe, the kitchen is exposed so you can see them working on the food. Bar has really good cocktails and the food is incredible
Upscaled German classics like schnitzel, spatzel and etc. Good German beer list. Friendly staff and a great time.

I usually hate pretzels but was blown away with the ones offered as an app. Everything we had as great and although it is German they had ample options that did not include pork which is something I look for in a restaurant. The portions are perfect and the staff was efficient and knowledgeable. Def a spot to go again.

Delicious Ribeye and Chicken!  Fun, professional staff 👍👍
Very well decorated and spacious inside. The food is delicious but don't expect generous portions.  Credit cards accepted and metered street parking only.
Good piggy collection
Our group tried almost everything on the menu and loved it.  Service was great too.

Great food!
